From e8812b6d7b42cd514e57465c9d901a70ee52f8f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Colin Watson <cjwatson@ubuntu.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Mar 2014 17:09:45 +0000
Subject: Remove limits on loop labels

There's no reason to impose any particular limit on loop labels, since
they just represent a single large partition.  Sector counts over 2^32
are needed for large RAID arrays.

Bug-Debian: http://bugs.debian.org/592679
Bug-Ubuntu: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/543838
Forwarded: http://lists.alioth.debian.org/pipermail/parted-devel/2010-August/003725.html
Last-Update: 2010-04-09

Patch-Name: loop-limits.patch
---
 libparted/labels/pt-limit.c     | 8 ++++----
 libparted/labels/pt-limit.gperf | 3 ++-
 tests/t9021-maxima.sh           | 2 +-
 3 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libparted/labels/pt-limit.c b/libparted/labels/pt-limit.c
index bda2ae4..1888f36 100644
